8—10. It was not unusual at the shows for the emperors to distribute refreshments to the spectatorS. This was done in three ways: (1) tickets were given entitling the holder to be served with provisions, comp. 1. 26. (2) eatables were handed round in small baskets (panaria and sportellae). These could apparently either be eaten on the spot or carried away. (3) Huge dishes were carried round from which the spectators helped themselves.
